There’s nothing quite like the satisfying crunch of a perfectly baked breadstick. Whether you enjoy them as a snack, a side for soups, or a complement to a cheese platter, homemade breadsticks are easy to make and taste far better than store-bought versions. In this guide, we’ll walk you through the process of making crispy, golden-brown breadsticks right in your kitchen.
Why Make Breadsticks at Home?
Making breadsticks at home allows you to control the ingredients, ensuring a healthier and fresher product. Plus, you can customize the flavors to your liking—whether you prefer classic garlic and parmesan or something more adventurous like rosemary and sea salt.
Ingredients You’ll Need
To make about 15-20 breadsticks, you’ll need the following ingredients:
For the Dough:
2 cups all-purpose flour (or bread flour for extra crispiness)
1 teaspoon salt
1 teaspoon sugar
1 teaspoon instant yeast
¾ cup warm water (110°F/43°C)
2 tablespoons olive oil
For the Topping (Optional but Recommended):
2 tablespoons melted butter
½ teaspoon garlic powder
½ teaspoon dried oregano or rosemary
¼ cup grated parmesan cheese (for a cheesy version)
Coarse sea salt for sprinkling
Step-by-Step Instructions
Step 1: Prepare the Dough
In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, salt, sugar, and instant yeast.
Add the warm water and olive oil, then mix until a rough dough forms.
Knead the dough for about 8-10 minutes until it becomes smooth and elastic. If the dough feels too sticky, add a little more flour; if too dry, add a tablespoon of water.
Place the dough in a lightly greased bowl, cover it with a clean kitchen towel, and let it rise for about an hour, or until doubled in size.
Step 2: Shape the Breadsticks
Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Once the dough has risen, punch it down and transfer it to a lightly floured surface.
Roll out the dough into a rectangle about ¼ inch thick.
Use a sharp knife or pizza cutter to slice the dough into strips (about ½ inch wide and 6 inches long).
Gently roll each strip between your palms to create a cylindrical shape.
Step 3: Bake the Breadsticks
Place the shaped dough sticks onto the prepared baking sheet, leaving some space between them.
Lightly brush the tops with melted butter and sprinkle with garlic powder, oregano, parmesan cheese, or coarse sea salt.
Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes, or until golden brown and crispy.
Step 4: Cool and Serve
Remove the breadsticks from the oven and let them cool slightly on a wire rack.
Serve them warm with marinara sauce, cheese dips, or as a side to your favorite meal.
Tips for Extra Crispy Breadsticks
Use Bread Flour: If you want an extra crunchy texture, opt for bread flour instead of all-purpose flour.
Roll Them Thin: The thinner the breadsticks, the crispier they will be. If you prefer a softer inside, roll them slightly thicker.
Bake Longer for Extra Crunch: If you want an even crispier texture, bake them for an additional 3-5 minutes at a lower temperature (375°F/190°C).
Brush with Olive Oil Before Baking: This adds a beautiful golden color and enhances crispiness.
Conclusion
Making crispy breadsticks at home is simple and rewarding. With just a few basic ingredients and a little patience, you can create delicious, golden-brown breadsticks that rival those from the best Italian restaurants. Experiment with different toppings and seasonings to find your perfect flavor combination.

